column5: Got these fellas at my 8th stop of the day. Let a couple go and lost another few, including one right at the hole that had to be over 6lbs. Throughout the day I marked some great schools, but not all seemed hungry. I called in most fish with the jigging rap and sealed the deal with a Williams half and half. The bottom one in the pic was 5lbs and the top one was 4 lbs 11 oz; both fought like absolute champs! Lots of fish out there, just have to get on them! Darcy
nice catch, darcy. glad to here there starting to show there face now.
Sounds like fun when you were able to locate them Great job darcyheitzner Thanks for sharing Leechman
